{"id":87402,"title":"Combined use of hyperbaric oxygen and sprayed keratinocyte suspension to tackle a difficult wound.","abstract":"This is the first reported case in the literature to combine the use of a well established therapy to achieve wound healing (ie hyperbaric oxygen treatment) and a novel sprayed keratinocyte suspension technique to treat a challenging wound successfully. The merits and potential issues associated with these treatments are outlined and the case is detailed. ","date":"2014-09-09","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25198965","annotations":[{"name":"Wound","weight":0.46934,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wound"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.391104,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Hyperbaric medicine","weight":0.154985,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperbaric_medicine"},{"name":"Oxygen","weight":0.153446,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen"},{"name":"Healing","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Healing"},{"name":"Literature","weight":0.0366575,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature"},{"name":"Keratinocyte","weight":0.0329831,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keratinocyte"},{"name":"Wound healing","weight":0.0310064,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wound_healing"},{"name":"Suspension (vehicle)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suspension_(vehicle)"},{"name":"Novel","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel"}]}
